THE INAUGURAL FNF/IRR LIBERTY LECTURE The Friedrich Naumann Foundation for Freedom (FNF) in conjunction with the Institute of Race Relations (IRR) will be hosting the inaugural FNF/IRR Liberty Lecture – a public lecture on freedom, which this year will coincide with the FNF’s 60th anniversary. YOU ARE CORDIALLY INVITED TO ATTEND. Lecture: Freedom and Victimhood Lecturer: Gareth van Onselen, head of politics and governance at the IRR DATES AND VENUES JOHANNESBURG Thursday 1 November 2018 The Country Club, 1 Napier Road, Auckland Park CAPE TOWN Thursday 8 November 2018 Easy City Studios, 7th _ oor, 62 Roeland Street, Gardens TIME: 6.00 pm for 6.30pm DRESS: Smart Casual SPACE IS LIMITED Please RSVP before the close of business on Friday 26 October 2018, to: KELEBOGILE LEEPILE Media & Public Affairs Officer kelebogile@sairr.org.za 011 482 7221 Ext. 2018 079 051 0073 Please remember to include whether you will be joining us in Johannesburg or Cape Town. 